docs.abstract: Democratic candidates are publicly aligning themselves with union members in hopes of holding onto their support — and winning over those who flipped for President Trump in 2016.
docs.snippet: Democratic candidates are publicly aligning themselves with union members in hopes of holding onto their support — and winning over those who flipped for President Trump in 2016.
docs.lead_paragraph: DETROIT — The Democratic presidential candidates have been chasing labor support all summer, appearing at small union halls and large conferences, and tweeting support for workers at companies like Amazon and Walmart. But now, as the United Automobile Workers, one of the nation’s largest unions, stages a strike that has even drawn words of support from President Trump, Democrats are seizing the moment to align themselves with workers in public and dramatic ways.

headline.main: Warren and Biden Join U.A.W. Picket Lines as Democrats Use Strike to Court Labor
headline.print_headline: Democrats Join U.A.W. Picketers in Show of Solidarity With Labor

docs.abstract: The recent shooting of a black resident by a white police officer has tested the city’s relationship with its mayor, Pete Buttigieg.
docs.snippet: The recent shooting of a black resident by a white police officer has tested the city’s relationship with its mayor, Pete Buttigieg.
docs.lead_paragraph: A special prosecutor was appointed Wednesday to investigate the fatal shooting of Eric J. Logan, an African-American man, by a white South Bend, Ind., police officer who did not have his body camera activated at the time.

headline.main: Special Prosecutor Is Assigned in South Bend Police Shooting
headline.print_headline: Special Prosecutor Is Set For South Bend Shooting

docs.abstract: John James, who received President Trump’s backing, won the Republican nomination for Senate as the president’s looming presence continued to influence the midterms.
docs.snippet: John James, who received President Trump’s backing, won the Republican nomination for Senate as the president’s looming presence continued to influence the midterms.
docs.lead_paragraph: DETROIT — Gretchen Whitmer, a former leader in the Michigan State Senate, captured the Democratic nomination for governor Tuesday night and will face off against the state’s Republican attorney general, Bill Schuette, in a race that looms as a pivotal test of whether Democrats can reclaim power in a state President Trump won two years ago.

headline.main: Whitmer and Schuette Win Michigan Governor’s Nominations
headline.print_headline: Primary Victories Set the Stage in Michigan for Stark Ideological Fights

docs.abstract: Ms. Warren said she had grown more comfortable talking about her experience over the years, explaining why her description of the 1971 episode in her stump speeches differs from how she discussed it in the past.
docs.snippet: Ms. Warren said she had grown more comfortable talking about her experience over the years, explaining why her description of the 1971 episode in her stump speeches differs from how she discussed it in the past.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — It is one of Elizabeth Warren’s signature anecdotes in her stump speech: By the end of her first year as a public-school teacher, she was “visibly pregnant,” and the principal wished her luck and hired another teacher to replace her.

headline.main: Elizabeth Warren Details Her Account of Losing Teaching Job Because of Pregnancy
headline.print_headline: Warren Details Account  Of Losing Teaching Job  Because of a Pregnancy

docs.abstract: The two Colorado politicians’ decisions to run for president added an element of sibling-style rivalry to the race.
docs.snippet: The two Colorado politicians’ decisions to run for president added an element of sibling-style rivalry to the race.
docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Michael Bennet and former Gov. John Hickenlooper have a longstanding personal and professional relationship, and their campaigns add an element of sibling-style rivalry to the race.

headline.main: John Hickenlooper Used to Be Michael Bennet’s Boss
